post_cb({"24472876": {"LastActivityDate": "2014-06-29T03:25:16.513", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>If you call <code>delete</code> on something that you didn't get back from <code>new</code>, that's <strong>undefined behavior</strong>.</p>\n<p>So the result of the following code is undefined:</p>\n<pre><code>int* ptr = new int[10];\nptr += 2;\ndelete[] ptr;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Let's look at the standard as well:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<h3>C++ 2011. Section 3.7.4.2 Deallocation functions. Paragraph 3.</h3>\n<p id=\"so_24472841_24472876_0\">Otherwise, the behavior is undefined if the value supplied to <code>operator delete(void*)</code> in the standard library is not one of the values returned by a previous invocation of either <code>operator new(std::size_t)</code> or <code>operator new(std::size_t, const std::nothrow_t&amp;)</code> in the standard library, and the behavior is undefined if the value supplied to <code>operator delete[](void*)</code> in the standard library is not one of the values returned by a previous invocation of either <code>operator new[](std::size_t)</code> or <code>operator new[](std::size_t, const std::nothrow_t&amp;)</code> in the standard library.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "CreationDate": "2014-06-29T03:20:41.910", "LastEditDate": "2014-06-29T03:25:16.513", "ParentId": "24472841", "Id": "24472876", "LastEditorUserId": "47453", "PostTypeId": "2", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "47453"}, "24472841": {"CreationDate": "2014-06-29T03:13:30.357", "ViewCount": "78", "FavoriteCount": "1", "Id": "24472841", "AcceptedAnswerId": "24472876", "Score": "0", "Title": "Deleting an array", "LastEditorUserId": "3234422", "CommentCount": "5", "Body": "<p>Let's suppose the following code:</p>\n<pre><code>    int* ptr = new int[10];\n    ...\n    ...\n    ptr += 2;\n    delete[] ptr;\n    ptr = NULL;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Should ptr be pointing on the first element of the array when the delete is called?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><arrays>", "LastEditDate": "2014-08-10T09:16:30.823", "LastActivityDate": "2014-08-10T09:16:30.823", "PostTypeId": "1", "AnswerCount": "1", "OwnerUserId": "3787028"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_24472841_24472876_0": {"length": 41, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 7182}}, "n3337": {"so_24472841_24472876_0": {"length": 41, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 6926}}}});